cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.TPLP 

This paper deals with the equational proofs of an imperative language, which involves reasoning about the behavior of computational effects and states. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Logic (cs.LO), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL), and Theory of Programming Languages (cs.TPLP) sub-categories.
